4f20bdaa-6035-4440-92b3-15c3c0d0435c.006949ab-e99b-41f1-99cb-7816c70be7a5.description=
Adds rows of data to an Excel document. This operation can be used to add/insert/update data to worksheets and documents. 
XLS, XLSX and XLSM formats are supported. 

Inputs\:
    excelFileName - The absolute path to the new Excel document.
Examples\: c\:\temp\test.xls
    worksheetName - The worksheet to which the data should be added.
Default value\: Sheet1 
    headerData - A delimited list of column names. If left blank, the document will not have a header for the data.
    rowData - A delimited list of data.
    columnDelimiter - A delimiter used to separate columns of rowData and headerData.
Default value\: comma (,)
    rowsDelimiter - A delimiter used to separate rows of rowData.
Default value\: pipe (|)
    rowIndex - A list of row indexes.
Examples\: 1\:3, 10, 15\:20,25
Default value\: append from the last row of the Excel worksheet.
    columnIndex - A list of column indexes.
Examples\: 1\:3, 10, 15\:20,25
Default value\: from index 0 in the Excel worksheet.
    overwriteData - true if existing data should be overwritten.
Default value\: false


Result\:
    returnResult - This is the primary output. Returns the number of rows that were added.

Responses\:
    success - One or more rows of data were added successfully.
    failure - Failed to add rows of data to the Excel document.


Notes\:
1. All the index inputs are 0 based.
2. If rowIndex input is not empty the row count must be equal to the row count of rowData.
3. If columnIndex input is not empty the column count must be equal to the column count of rowData
4. If columnIndex input is not empty it's used for every row that is added.
5. If the rowData contains a numeric value, the cell modified is set to numeric type.
6. There's a limitation that if the rowData is a date or time value, the operation treats it as a string value.
7. If there's any change in the worksheet, all values of formula type cells are updated.
8. If there's any merged region existed in the worksheet, only the top left cell can be modified.

Examples\:
1. To add a header and a single row of data to an Excel document using comma as the column delimiter, input should be given as follows-
headerData - columnName1,columnName2,columnName3
rowData - value1,value2,value3
columnDelimiter - ,

2. To add a header and multiple rows of data to an Excel document using comma (,) as the column delimiter and pipe (|) as the row delimiter, input should be given as follows-
headerData 	- columnName1,columnName2,columnName3
rowData - value11,value12,value13|value21,value22,value23|value31,value32,value33
columnDelimiter - ,
rowDelimiter	- |

3. To add multiple rows of data on multiple columns to an Excel document using comma (,) as the column delimiter and pipe (|) as the row delimiter, input should be given as follows-
rowData - value11,value12,value13|value21,value22,value23|value31,value32,value33
columnDelimiter - ,
rowDelimiter	- |
rowIndex - 1,3,4
columnIndex - 3\:5
4f20bdaa-6035-4440-92b3-15c3c0d0435c.04934c2e-e4e0-471a-8b08-74f848495b4f.description=
Deletes the file or directory specified.

Input Parameters\:
source - full path to file/directory to be removed (can be a UNC path)
user - Username to use for thread impersonation on the RAS host while deleting.
password - Password for the user.

Responses\:
success - The specified path was successfuly removed.
failure - Unable to remove file/directory.
4f20bdaa-6035-4440-92b3-15c3c0d0435c.377ee18a-549f-4da9-9924-3f6587702dfd.description=
 
Check to see if the value stored in a specified flow variable, denoted by key, is null.

Inputs\:
    keyName - The key to check, i.e. the name of the flow variable. 
    trimSpaces - If set on "true" then all the whitespaces will be removed from the value stored. 
Valid values\: true, false
Default value\: false

Returns\: 
    The value in the specified key, i.e. flow variable with all whitespaces removed.

Responses\:
    isNull - If the key is a null pointer, i.e. the flow variable doesn't have an assigned value.
    notNull - If some value is stored in the key, i.e the flow variable has a value assigned. 

Notes\: 
    1. If the "trimSpaces" input is set on "true" and the value from "keyName" contains only whitespaces then the response will be "isNull". 
    2. If the "trimSpaces" input is set on "false" and the value from "keyName" contains only whitespaces then the response will be "notNull". 
    3. If any other value than "true" or "false" is passed on "trimSpaces" input then the default value (false) will be used.

4f20bdaa-6035-4440-92b3-15c3c0d0435c.description=Identify the active row in VMGD when Fixed Flag is set to No. Inputs\: screenVMGD - The screen dump of VMGD. worksheetName - The name of the worksheet in Excel spreadsheet. excelFileName - The path and filename of the Excel spreadsheet. Eg\: C\:\Temp\filename.xlsx Returns\: rowsCount - Total number of rows in VMGD rowsIndex - Row numbers where SHDE entries are present. activeLine - The line number where values need to be pushed. Responses\: success - The flow completed as stated in description. failure - The flow failed to complete. 4f20bdaa-6035-4440-92b3-15c3c0d0435c.ede09ea9-4b14-44cd-821e-2573db901c58.description=
Creates a blank Excel spreadsheet document. The format of the document (XLS or XLSX) depends on the extension used by the file.

Inputs\:
    excelFileName - The absolute path to the new Excel document.
Examples\: c\:\temp\test.xls
    worksheetNames - A delimited list of names that will be created as worksheets in the document. 
Default value\: Sheet1,Sheet2,Sheet3.
    delimiter - The character used to delimit worksheet names.
Default value\: comma (,)

Result\:
    returnResult - This is the primary output. Returns a success or failure message.

Responses\:
    success - A new Excel document is created successfully.
    failure - Failed to create a new Excel document.

Notes\:
XLSM format is not supported.
4f20bdaa-6035-4440-92b3-15c3c0d0435c.f393e3d1-2ca7-4d8f-a4b7-1c102477c3f4.description=
Retrieves row indexes if the row satisfies the specified condition in an Excel document. 
XLS, XLSX and XLSM formats are supported. 

Inputs\: 
    excelFileName - The absolute path to the new Excel document.
Examples\: c\:\temp\test.xls
    worksheetName - The name of Excel worksheet.
Default value\: Sheet1
    hasHeader - If Yes, then the first row of the document is expected to be the header row.
Valid values\: yes, no
Default value\: yes
    firstRowIndex - The index of the first row in the Excel worksheet, including the header row.
Default value\: 0
    columnIndextoQuery - The column index to search in.
    operator - The math operators. 
Valid values\: \=\=, \!\= for string comparison; \=\=, \!\=, <,<\=,>,>\= for numeric comparison.
Default vaue\: \=\=
    value - The value to search in the specified column. If left blank, it means an empty value.

Results\: 
    returnResult - This is the primary result. Return a list of row indexes that satisfied the specified condition.
    rowsCount - The number of the row indexes returned.

Responses\: 
    success - The row indexes were retrieved successfully. 
    failure - Failed to retrieve the row indexes.

Notes\:
1. All the index inputs are 0 based.
2. Observed that in some Excel worksheet, the first couple of rows are used for title. So added firstRowIndex input.
3. Value in date type has to be in the format of "YYYY/MM/DD", "YYYY/DD/MM HH\:MM\:SS" or "YYYY/MM/DD HH\:MM".
4. Value in time type has to be in the format of "HH\:MM\:SS" or "HH\:MM".
5. If there's any merged region existed in the worksheet, the cells in the merged region are not considered except the top left cell.
